---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/site';

const description = 'Privacy Policy for The Reichmann Co. How we collect, use, store and protect your personal information.';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy · The Reichmann Co."
  description={description}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container container-prose">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
        <span aria-current="page">Privacy</span>
      </nav>
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: 8 June 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-prose legal-doc">
      <section>
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          The Reichmann Co. (Pty) Ltd (formerly Reichmann Holdings (Pty) Ltd, Registration Number {SITE.registration})
          (&ldquo;The Reichmann Co.&rdquo;, &ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;, &ldquo;our&rdquo;) operates the website
          <a href={SITE.url}>thereichmannco.co.za</a> (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;).
          This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, share and protect your personal information
          when you visit the Site or interact with our services.
        </p>
        <p>
          This Policy is published in accordance with the Protection of Personal Information Act, 2013
          (POPIA), and, where applicable, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) of the European
          Union. By using our Site, you consent to the collection and use of your information in accordance
          with this Policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
        <h3>2.1 Information you provide directly</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact form submissions:</strong> name, email address, company name (optional), subject category, and message content.</li>
          <li><strong>Early access signup submissions:</strong> email address.</li>
          <li><strong>Email correspondence:</strong> any personal information you include when emailing us at info@thereichmannco.co.za.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>2.2 Information collected automatically</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Server and operational logs:</strong> basic technical information such as IP address, browser type, device type, referrer URL, and pages visited. This is collected by our hosting provider for security, abuse prevention, and operational purposes.</li>
          <li><strong>Browser local storage:</strong> we store your theme preference (light or dark) in your browser&rsquo;s local storage. This data is stored only on your device and is not transmitted to us.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>2.3 Information collected by the Lumarix application</h3>
        <p>
          When you use Lumarix, our Windows accounting application, including during the free trial, the app
          contacts our licensing service over the internet to check or activate your licence and to keep your
          account supported. During these checks it sends:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>your company name, and registration number where you have entered one;</li>
          <li>your business contact details where you have entered them (VAT number, address, email and phone), so we can support your account and invoice you accurately;</li>
          <li>a random installation identifier generated on your device, so we can recognise the installation across checks;</li>
          <li>a one-way hash of your Windows machine identifier, so we can anchor your free trial to this device and limit repeated trials;</li>
          <li>the number of active user accounts in the company file; and</li>
          <li>the version of Lumarix you are running.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We use this to manage and activate licences, support your account, and confirm that seat usage stays
          within your licence. Your accounting data itself (customers, suppliers, invoices, ledgers and the like)
          stays in your local company file on your own device and is not sent to us.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. How we use your information</h2>
        <p>We use your personal information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Responding to enquiries submitted via our contact form.</li>
          <li>Sending the transactional welcome email confirming receipt of an early access signup.</li>
          <li>Notifying early access participants when our products are ready for them.</li>
          <li>Managing, activating and supporting Lumarix software licences, and confirming that licensed seat usage stays within the agreed limits.</li>
          <li>Communicating with you regarding our services and any related business matters.</li>
          <li>Improving the Site&rsquo;s functionality, security, and user experience.</li>
          <li>Complying with our legal and regulatory obligations.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not use your personal information for direct marketing without your explicit consent, and we do not
          sell, rent, or trade your personal information with third parties.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Lawful basis for processing (POPIA Section 11)</h2>
        <p>We process your personal information on the following lawful grounds:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Your consent</strong>, provided when you submit a form or contact us.</li>
          <li><strong>Performance of a contract</strong>, or steps taken at your request prior to entering into a contract.</li>
          <li><strong>Our legitimate interests</strong> in operating, maintaining, securing, and improving our business, where such interests are not overridden by your rights.</li>
          <li><strong>Compliance with applicable law</strong>.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Third-party service providers</h2>
        <p>
          We use the following trusted third-party services to operate the Site and our services. Each provider
          processes your personal information only to the extent necessary to perform its specific role, and is
          bound by its own privacy obligations.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Vercel Inc.</strong> (United States): website hosting, content delivery, and serverless function infrastructure.</li>
          <li><strong>Formspree, Inc.</strong> (United States): processing of contact form submissions.</li>
          <li><strong>Resend, Inc.</strong> (United States): delivery of transactional emails, including the early access signup welcome email and admin notifications.</li>
          <li><strong>Upstash, Inc.</strong> (United States): managed Redis (key-value) storage for Lumarix licence and activation records.</li>
          <li><strong>Diamatrix CC trading as Domains.co.za</strong> (South Africa): domain registration, DNS hosting, and email mailbox hosting for our info@thereichmannco.co.za mailbox.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Each provider maintains its own privacy policy governing how it handles personal information. We
          recommend reviewing those policies if you wish to understand their practices in detail.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. International data transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Some of our service providers are located outside the Republic of South Africa, including in the United
          States. When your personal information is transferred outside South Africa, we take reasonable steps to
          ensure such transfers comply with POPIA Section 72, including reliance on the contractual terms with
          these providers and their published commitments to data protection.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes for which it was
          collected, or as required by law.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact form submissions:</strong> retained for up to 24 months from the date of submission, unless ongoing communication or business reasons require a longer period.</li>
          <li><strong>Early access signup details:</strong> retained until the launch of the relevant product plus 12 months, or until you request deletion.</li>
          <li><strong>Server and operational logs:</strong> typically retained for up to 90 days by our hosting provider.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          After the applicable retention period, your personal information is deleted or anonymised in
          accordance with our internal procedures.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Your rights under POPIA</h2>
        <p>You have the following rights in relation to your personal information:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>To be notified that your personal information is being collected.</li>
          <li>To access the personal information we hold about you.</li>
          <li>To request the correction or update of inaccurate or incomplete personal information.</li>
          <li>To request the deletion or destruction of your personal information.</li>
          <li>To object, on reasonable grounds, to the processing of your personal information.</li>
          <li>To withdraw consent at any time, where processing is based on consent (without affecting the lawfulness of processing before withdrawal).</li>
          <li>To lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator of South Africa.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
          <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>. We will respond
          within a reasonable period and as required by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement reasonable technical and organisational measures to safeguard your personal information
          against loss, unauthorised access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. These measures include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Encryption in transit (HTTPS / TLS).</li>
          <li>Use of reputable infrastructure and service providers with established security standards.</li>
          <li>Limiting access to personal information to authorised personnel on a need-to-know basis.</li>
          <li>Storing credentials and API keys as protected environment variables rather than in source code.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          No method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is completely secure.
          While we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
        <p>We do not use tracking, advertising, or marketing cookies on this Site.</p>
        <p>
          Our hosting provider may set first-party cookies that are strictly necessary for operating the Site
          securely. Your browser may also store a theme preference (light or dark) in browser local storage;
          this is stored only on your device and is not personal information.
        </p>
        <p>
          If we introduce analytics, performance, or marketing technologies in future, we will update this
          Policy and provide appropriate opt-out mechanisms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Children&rsquo;s privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The Site and our services are not directed to individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from minors. If you become aware that a minor has provided us with
          personal information, please contact us so that we can take appropriate action.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>12. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, the services
          we use, or applicable law. The &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date at the top of this page indicates when the Policy
          was last revised.
        </p>
        <p>
          We encourage you to review this Policy periodically. Material changes will be communicated by
          posting a prominent notice on the Site or, where appropriate, by direct notification to
          registered users.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>13. Information Officer and contact details</h2>
        <p>
          In accordance with POPIA, the Information Officer of The Reichmann Co. (Pty) Ltd is responsible for
          encouraging compliance with the Act and handling requests regarding personal information. For any
          questions, requests, or concerns about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your personal information,
          please contact:
        </p>
        <div class="legal-contact-block">
          <p><strong>The Reichmann Co. (Pty) Ltd</strong></p>
          <p>Formerly: Reichmann Holdings (Pty) Ltd</p>
          <p>Registration Number: {SITE.registration}</p>
          <p>Email: <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a></p>
          <p>Registered in: South Africa</p>
        </div>
        <p>You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator of South Africa:</p>
        <div class="legal-contact-block">
          <p><strong>The Information Regulator (South Africa)</strong></p>
          <p>JD House, 27 Stiemens Street, Braamfontein, Johannesburg, 2001</p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:complaints.IR@justice.gov.za">complaints.IR@justice.gov.za</a></p>
          <p>Website: <a href="https://inforegulator.org.za" target="_blank" rel="noopener">inforegulator.org.za</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <p class="legal-back">
        <a href="/" class="legal-back-link">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.25" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <line x1="19" y1="12" x2="5" y2="12"></line>
            <polyline points="12 19 5 12 12 5"></polyline>
          </svg>
          Back to home
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-meta {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .legal-doc section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .legal-doc h2 {
    font-size: var(--fs-2xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .legal-doc h3 {
    font-size: var(--fs-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .legal-doc p,
  .legal-doc li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
  }

  .legal-doc p { margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }

  .legal-doc ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    list-style: disc;
  }

  .legal-doc li { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }

  .legal-doc a {
    color: var(--brand-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal-contact-block {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    background: var(--bg-subtle);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--brand-primary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
  .legal-contact-block p { margin-bottom: var(--space-1); }

  .legal-back {
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    padding-top: var(--space-6);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }
  .legal-back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: var(--fw-medium);
  }
  .legal-back-link:hover { color: var(--brand-primary); }
</style>
